unwound.title: HackCity18
unwound.description: HackCity is back again for it's second year! We are welcoming students from all over London, the UK and Europe, for a all student fun and free Hackathon.  We have some amazing sponsors lined up, so everything is provided free - all you have to do it get your ticket!  Format of the Weekend... Enjoy 24 hours of hacking, open to build anything you like. Challenges will also be provided but we encourage people to think outside the box. We will have student and sponsor led workshops to introduce various technologies such as:  Web development & Unity (may vary). You can hack in teams up to 4 persons, or alone if you prefer, however if you have more than 4 team members you will be exempt from winning prizes. Leading on to prizes... Hackers will be given a period at the end to present their project, what they made and how they made it, what tech they used and if they had any problems. This year, we are providing some cool new gadgets for attendees to hack with, such as motion sensors, bluetooth beacons and raspberry pies! HackCity is free of charge, food and refreshments will be provided and paid for by our awesome sponsors as well as prizes and challenges.  We hope to see you soon!  By purchasing a ticket for HackCity, you will automatically agree to abide by the code of conduct listed on our website, as well as any rules we provide on the day.    FAQs   Are there ID or minimum age requirements to enter the event? Yes, we require you to bring along your student ID. You also must be over 18 to attend HackCity18 - sorry kids.    What are my transportation/parking options for getting to and from the event? As we are in London, there are many tube stations close by, closest being Angle (Northern Line) with a 4 minute walk to the venue. There are unfortuantly NO parking spaces for drivers.  Do you provide travel reimbursements? Unfortuantly not this year, however something we are hoping to do soon.  Check out the website for more detials - www.hackcity.org
